Daniel Agger has revealed he will consider his Liverpool future if he's not in boss Brendan Rodgers' first-team plans next season.

The 29-year-old endured a frustrating campaign at Anfield last year, often filling in as cover for Rodgers' preferred centre-back partnership of Mamadou Sakho and Martin Skrtel.

