The Denmark international made only 20 Premier League appearances as the Reds finished second at the end of the 2013/14 campaign, and has warned he may seek a move away from Merseyside if his first-team prospects don't improve.

'It is no secret that I had problems last season and I am considering things,' he reportedly told a Danish newspaper.

'How things turned out last season is not acceptable for me.

'I am here now and it is up to me to show the coach that I should play.'

